         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958"/><citedRange>300</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1981"/><citedRange>490</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:mullerandsieg1916"/></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2 #a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>165</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>213</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>469</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1991"/><citedRange>23</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>28</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>214</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Welche da jetzt ... in des Buddha Gesetz Freude finden ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever] now ... take delight in the Law of the Buddha ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever] now ... take delight in the Law of the Buddha ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>196</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Welche da jetzt ... in des Buddha Gesetz Freude finden ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever] now ... take delight in the Law of the Buddha ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Who[ever] now ... take delight in the Law of the Buddha ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>196</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4 #b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>404</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>114f, 296, 356ff, 4</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Welche da jetzt ... (entlassen) habend, in des Buddha Gesetz Freude empfinden, Gaben (ge)ben, sittliche Haltung bewahren, das Wissen l(ernen), der Juwelendreiheit Dienste tun, Höhle, Zelle, Kloster [oder] Aufenthaltsort der Gemeinde bauen, elende Wesen (lieb)en, den Kranken Dienst tun, an ... Gefallen haben, ... Wissen lehren/lernen, vom (Bö)sen fernhalten [und] an die Tugend binden, ebendiese (werden) zu (der Zei)t mit dem Bu(ddha, dem Lehrer), zusammenkommen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Those who now ... having (released), find pleasure in the law of the Buddha, (gi)ve donations, keep the moral conduct, l(earn) the knowledge, do service to the jewel-trinity, build a cave, a cell, a monastery [or] a habitation for the community, (lo)ve miserable beings, do service to the sick, find pleasure in ..., teach/learn the knowledge, keep away from (ev)il [and] attach to the virtues, these very [people] (will), at (that tim)e, meet with the Bu(ddha, the teacher).</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>144-5, 356-9, 404, 461, 501</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4 (+ b6)"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... welche da jetzt ... an die Tugenden binden ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">however now attaches ... to the virtues ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>296</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>175</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>359</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they preserve the morality and learn the knowledge</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>23 n.1</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a260"/> (completing); MaitrHami 16, 12-13; MaitrSiŋgim, Taf. 161. 162, 51</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment, which complements <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a260"/>, contains part of the sixteenth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka. Uy. parallels are MaitrHami 16, 12a26-13b19, and MaitrSiŋgim, Taf. 161, 162, 51 (<bibl><title corresp="ref:tekin1980"/><citedRange>139-143</citedRange></bibl>). Immediately followed by <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a266"/>+<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a276"/>. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>202-203</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="philcomment"><bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1994c"/><citedRange>378f</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of a manuscript which includes A 251 - A 294 (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:gengetal2004a"/><citedRange>64-65</citedRange></bibl>). Lines a7-8 and b1 are lost.</note></p>
         </div>
